# SUMMARY REPORT

### 1) Hourly energy consumption 
![Energy consumption per hour](visuals/Average_hourly_power_consumption.png)

Key Insights
Energy use shows two clear peaks:
Morning (7–8 AM): household preparation activities.
Evening (8 PM peak): highest consumption due to cooking, entertainment, and general household activity.
Lowest usage occurs during early morning hours (12 AM – 5 AM).

Recommendations
Introduce time-of-use pricing to shift demand away from peak hours.
Encourage the use of energy-efficient cooking and heating appliances.
Promote smart scheduling of high-energy devices outside peak periods.

### 2)Distribution of Global Active Power
![Distribution of Global Active Power](visuals/Global_active_power_distribution.png)

Key Insights
Consumption is bimodal, showing two distinct usage states:
Low usage (idle/off-peak periods)
High usage (active household periods)
Majority of consumption is concentrated at lower levels, with occasional high spikes.

Recommendations
Investigate appliances contributing to high-consumption peaks.
Promote load balancing habits (avoid running multiple heavy appliances simultaneously).
Use smart monitoring tools to help households track spikes.

### 3) Average Daily Consumption
![Average Daily Energy Consumption](visuals/Average_daily_power_consumption.png)

Key Insights
Highest energy usage occurs on weekends (especially Saturday).
Lowest usage observed on weekdays and is especially low on Thursdays.
Indicates strong influence of household routines and occupancy patterns.

Recommendations
Target weekend-focused energy awareness campaigns.
Utilities should plan for higher weekend demand capacity.
Encourage shifting non-essential activities to off-peak weekdays.

### 4) Monthly Energy Consumption
![Monthly energy consumption](visuals/Average_monthly_power_consumption.png)

Key Insights
Consumption declines from early months (Jan) toward mid-year, then rises toward year-end.
Suggests seasonal variation, likely due to weather and holiday activity.

Recommendations
Plan grid capacity for end-of-year demand increases.
Schedule maintenance during low-demand months.
Launch seasonal energy-saving campaigns.

