Investigate unusual residual spikes for anomalies.

### 7)  24-Hour Moving Average Trend
![24-Hour Moving Average Trend](visuals/24_hour_moving_average_forecast.png)

Key Insights
Clear and stable daily cycle (wave-like pattern).
Confirms electricity usage follows a predictable daily rhythm.

Recommendations
Use pattern for demand forecasting and planning.
Optimize energy distribution around expected peak hours.
Improve predictive maintenance scheduling.

## Key Takeaways
1) Electricity usage is highly behavior-driven, with strong daily and weekly cycles.
2) Clear peak demand periods occur in mornings and evenings.
3) Consumption is predictable and stable enough for accurate forecasting.
4) Occasional spikes exist but are mostly normal household behavior.

### Strategic Recommendations

#### 1) Demand Management
Implement time-of-use tariffs.
Encourage shifting consumption away from peak hours.

#### 2) Customer Behavior
Promote energy-efficient appliances.
Run awareness campaigns focused on evening and weekend usage.

#### 3) Grid Planning
Increase capacity planning for evenings and weekends.
Prepare for seasonal peaks (end-of-year demand surge).




